<strong>All vehicles, RVsâ€™ and boats</strong> entering the park must be properly licensed and insured. Management reserves the right to approve all units to be accommodated at the park.

<strong>Management is not responsible</strong> for damage, injury, or loss to either person or property. The owner/management of Presnellâ€™s Bayside Marina and RV Resort absolve themselves from all liability and responsibility pertaining to loss by fire, theft, weather, acts of God, property damage, accident or any other cause whatsoever, and guest agree to save, protect and hold harmless Presnellâ€™s Vacation Resort and RV Park LLC from all such liability.

<strong>Check in/out time</strong> â€“ Check in Time is 3:00 PM for RVs and 4:00 PM for Cottages. Check out time is 11:00 AM - Late checkouts may lose their deposit and or be charged for Â½ of a day rate. Please pre-register for additional days as soon as possible but no later than 10:00 AM. Car passes must be displayed at all times. Per Florida Law no one under the age of 18 may rent a camp site.

<strong>Please only one camping unit and two vehicles per site.</strong> See office for additional vehicle parking arrangements. Please do not park in unrented sites or in roadways, as they must remain open for RV and vehicle traffic. There is extra parking across the road. We reserve the right to tow a vehicle at the owners' expense if necessary.

<strong>Subleasing</strong> - of sites or units is prohibited. Site or unit rentals are not transferable.

<strong>Reservations are encouraged.</strong> If you request a specific lot we reserve the right to re-assign space if necessary in order to maximize our rental potential. Rates are subject to change without notice.

<strong>Cancellations</strong>
<ul>
 	<li>There is a 7 day cancellation notice requirement for nightly reservations. 14 day notice required.</li>
 	<li>There is a 14 day cancellation notice requirement for weekly reservations. 30 day notice required.</li>
 	<li>There is a 30 day cancellation notice requirement for monthly reservations. 45 day notice required.</li>
 	<li>Cancellations after Notice Requirement, Loss of deposit</li>
</ul>
<strong>Prices include 4 people</strong>. There is a $3.00 per day charge for any additional group/family member for each person over 5 years of age. The maximum number of people per site is 6.

<strong>Visitors</strong> - All visitors must register at office and receive a pass. Temporary or outside guests can pay $10 each per day to use facilities provided they are accompanied by a camping customer. All guests must leave by 10:00 PM or pay an additional charge.

<strong>Customer responsibility</strong> - Any customer or guest destroying/damaging park or other customerâ€™s property will be required to make restitution. If your RV has an electrical problem creating a problem with the park electric and a certified electrician has to be called you will be responsible for the cost of the electricianâ€™s service call and damages.

<strong>Tropical storms and hurricanes</strong> may require you to vacate the park if there is a mandatory evacuation or if management deems it unsafe for you to stay. Please familiarize yourself with a copy of the evacuation plan on line and or at the office. There are no refunds due to weather. However vouchers may be given for mandatory evacuation.

<strong>Please place trash</strong> in plastic bags and dispose of garbage in dumpsters and do not throw personal garbage in restrooms, laundry, club house or other building trash cans.

<strong>Quiet Hours</strong> are 10:00 PM TO 8:00 AM. Please observe these hours for everyoneâ€™s enjoyment.

<strong>Speed limit is 5 MPH</strong>. Please keep it Slow for everyoneâ€™s safety!

<strong>Weekly Rates</strong> are for 7 Nights - <strong>Monthly Rates</strong> are typically for 30 nights, plus or minus 1 night.

<strong>Monthly guest</strong> in consideration of all of our nightly guests and the fact that we are not a mobile home park; we do ask and expect everyone to follow these guidelines and rules. Exception to the guidelines will only be made by the manager. Violators of these guidelines and rules will be given a chance to rectify the problems. If the problems persist they will be asked to leave the park with no refund.

<strong>A $100 Electric deposit</strong> is required in advance for November - February Monthly Rentals for all separately metered sites. All rent must be paid on the date due a month in advance. Early departures revert to the price of nightly or weekly rate unless the full month is paid for. Metered sites will be read and paid for at the time the rent is due. The electric rate is $0.10254 cents per kilowatt for the first 1,000 kilowatts and $0.12616 kilowatts for over 1,000 kilowatts. (Rate subject to change per Power Company charges) Please confirm your meter reading at time of departure. Your electric deposit will be returned at your departure, provided all outstanding bills are paid and current and the site is fully cleaned or deposit will be applied to balance. Cash deposits may be sent back to you by mail by check.

<strong>Pets</strong>
<ul>
 	<li>Pet owners are allowed a maximum of 2 pets at the RV sites if management is notified at time of registration.</li>
 	<li>Pets are welcome. However, they must be kept on a leash, kept quit, and feces cleaned up immediately and disposed of in containers marked for such.</li>
 	<li>Pets are not allowed in cabins, park models, buildings, playground, or pool area.</li>
 	<li>Pets are not to be left unattended, with or without leash, outside of your RV.</li>
 	<li>Management is not responsible for the injury of your pet for any reason.</li>
 	<li>No mean or aggressive pets allowed in the park.</li>
 	<li>If your pet is loud you will be asked to leave.</li>
 	<li>All pets must have current vaccinations.</li>
 	<li>No outside cages please.</li>
</ul>
<strong>Pool Rules
</strong>
<ul>
 	<li>Swimming pool rules are posted at the swimming pool.</li>
 	<li>NO DIVING, running or horseplay in the pool or pool area.</li>
 	<li>Children under 16 and non-swimmers must be under adult supervision at all times.</li>
 	<li>Pool Hours are 8:00 AM to 10:00 PM. Swim at your own risk - NO LIFEGUARD ON DUTY.</li>
 	<li>Everyone must shower off before entering pool and spray off any floating devices, especially if either has been in saltwater. Saltwater damages the pool and may require shutting pool down until repaired.</li>
 	<li>No food, drinks, glass, breakable containers, or pets are allowed in or on the pool deck by Florida State Law.</li>
 	<li>Pool will be monitored, tested and occasionally closed for treatment as needed, per Florida Health Dept. regulations.</li>
 	<li>No baby diapers are allowed in the pools. Little swimmers or other appropriate swimwear must be worn. No pants, shorts or cut offs. Only proper swimming attire is permitted in pool or spa.</li>
</ul>
<strong>Marina No Wake Zone</strong> in boat basin and canal out 100 yards. Please no mooring in someone elseâ€™s space.

<strong>Parents</strong> are responsible for the whereabouts, safety and conduct of their children at all times so keep an eye on them please. All minors must have adult supervision after 9:00 PM.

<strong>No washing</strong> of vehicles, RVsâ€™ or boats etc. at camp sites.

<strong>Fireworks</strong> are prohibited per Florida Law.

<strong>Per Florida Law</strong> no clotheslines are allowed. Please do not attach anything to trees without approval from office.

<strong>No Smoking</strong> in any campground building, park model or cabin. When smoking, outside, please do not litter and please place cigarette butts only in containers marked for such.

<strong>No alcohol</strong> in pool area please.

<strong>Golf Carts</strong> -Please be respectful of other campers and do not drive your cart through campsites or common areas.

<strong>Valuable Items</strong> should be safely stored away. We are not responsible for stolen or lost items.

